framework.utilities

Class ObjectMap

  • java.lang.Object
    • framework.utilities.ObjectMap

  • public class ObjectMap
extends java.lang.Object
    This class provides functionality for reading locator information in from a property file. The file must end with ".properties". The file consists of rows of properties. Each property record has the following syntax: PROPERTY_NAME=LOCATOR_TYPE>LOCATOR_VALUE e.g. button_1=id>btn1
    Author:
    nvonop

    • Constructor Detail

      • ObjectMap

        public ObjectMap(java.lang.String mapFile)
        This constructor loads a set of Properties from a file matching the name of mapFile. These properties consist of various locator strings to uniquely identify UI controls on a page.
        Parameters:
        mapFile - The name of the properties file containing UI locator strings

    • Method Detail

      • getLocatorFromMap

        public org.openqa.selenium.By getLocatorFromMap(java.lang.String elementName)
                                         throws java.lang.Exception
        This method returns a new locator object based on the locator type and locator substring values from the property named elementName.
        Parameters:
        elementName - The name of the property containing the relevant locator information
        Returns:
        a By object consisting of the locator type and locator string
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - To indicate the locator type could not be determined

      • getLocatorAndOverride

        public org.openqa.selenium.By getLocatorAndOverride(java.lang.String logicalElementName,
                                           java.lang.String locatorValue)
                                             throws java.lang.Exception
        This method returns a new locator object based on the locator type value from the property named elementName and locatorName. This is useful if the locator value is dynamic but the locator type is known.
        Parameters:
        logicalElementName - The name of the property containing the relevant locator information
        locatorValue - The locator String value of the property
        Returns:
        a By object consisting of the locator type and locator string
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - To indicate the locator type could not be determined

      • getLocatorString

        public java.lang.String getLocatorString(java.lang.String logicalElementName)
        This method extracts the locator value from the property matching logicalElementName. It is useful if you want to modify the locator value in some way or add dynamic information using the getLocatorAndOverride method.
